name: Kitchener-Waterloo Little Theatre
directions: Two bathrooms off the lobby: one is a large one-toilet accessible bathroom, the other is a two-stall (one assessible) bathroom. Both unisex.  Previously men's and women's but both converted to unisex a few years ago.
comment: Irregular hours: only open during show nights (a few Thursday, Friday, Saturdays a month)

name: Canadian Rockies International Airport
directions: Two of them, one on the north end of the terminal, the other at the south end between the Men's & Women's rooms
comment: Free for all to use, both single stall unisex

name: Rarig Center
directions: Basement floor, single stall restroom
comment: In University of Minnesota building. Open to the public during week days

name: Hathaway Brown
directions: In middle school (atrium) right next to the aspire office.
comment: It is a school, so you know I wouldn't go in just to pee. But if you are there just know there is a gender neutral bathroom for use. Sorry this isn't more helpful.

name: Ocho Placas Tattoo Co.
directions: First floor: Last door on the right: Second floor, located in the last room.
comment: Must be a customer or their guest.

name: McMinnville Public Library
directions: Main floor, to the left of the reception desk

name: Orange County Community College
directions: On the first floor past the big staircase down the hallway on the left

name: Hancher Auditorium
directions:
First, second, and third floors, there is a large accessible single seat family restroom located near the gendered multi person restrooms.

On the first floor it's on the north side of the building just west of the elevators.

On the second floor it's in the hallway between the cafe and the grand stairs.

On the third floor it's across from the concession counter on the right.
comment: The first floor should be open during box office hours, restrooms are before ticket checks during shows.

name: University at Buffalo-Greiner Hall
street: John James Audubon Pkwy & Core Road
directions: First floor go through the main entrance, take the first left and it's on the left hand side

name: Byrne Dairy
directions: On the right when you go through the door, around the corner. There are signs
comment: Working here currently, none of us care which bathroom you want to go in, they are both identical. One is just labelled male  and the other female

name: The Filling Station (boutique pet supply store)
directions: One restroom, single stall. At the back of the store, down a short hall. Not terribly busy.
comment: Employees appear to be LGBT and LGBTQ-friendly. Also, their products are great. :)

name: Roche Bros
directions: On the far right in the front as soon as you enter.

name: The Uptown Nightclub
directions: Unisex handicap accessible single stall between gendered restrooms.
comment: Open 8PM to 2AM, cover charge during shows.

name: The Mall of Monroe
directions: Family restroom by the Phoenix Theater entrance.

name: Family Dollar
directions: Through double doors in back, second door on the left.
comment: Double doors say employees only, but restroom is open to public.

name: The House of Ink
directions: In the back of the shop.
comment: Open to anyone, don't have to be a customer.

name: Baddies Cafe
directions: Downstairs
comment: Staff are super friendly and it's a good idea to ask since it is a small business.

name: Catalyst Cafe
directions: By the stairs that go to the second floor.
comment: Have to be a paying customer at the place but their treats and coffee are to go and really friendly staff :)

name: Casita Taquetia
comment: Lgbtqiaa friendly! The giant rainbow flags will guide the way.  Prefers paying customers.

name: Bounty on Broad
directions: Upstairs restrooms
comment: Must be customer

name: The Castle
comment: Night club, usually pay to get in. Opens late.  Lgbtqiaa friendly

name: Wraps Mexican Grille
comment: Prefers paying costumer.  Very lgbtqiaa friendly. Family owned with close connection to transgender community.

name: E&D Games, in gulf view mall
comment: In the back of the shop.  Would prefer paying customers as the mall has a public restroom but an understanding family runs the store that is lgbtqiaa friendly

name: Bantam King Ramen
directions: All the way in the back of the restaurant
comment: They're all the way in the back of the restaurant. I went in as a paying customer, but I'm sure if you ask super nicely, they'll allow you, since the staff is very sweet.

name: Obsidian
directions: At the back of the cafe, 2 small multistall restrooms that are gendered but have large signs proclaiming that trans guests are supported and can use whichever bathroom they want.

name: Brits Pub
comment: The owners are very friendly, had no issues using the restrooms there before I had even shared my story with them.  It sounded like a close connection of theirs is transgender but I missed the start of their story due to noise.

name: Union trust building
directions: Second floor across from elevators also next to giant glass doors
comment: Ignore the sign saying no access on the stairs. Only entrance is from the side.

name: Kum and Go
directions: Back behind the donut case by the counter.
comment: Just lock the door behind you. Men's has a stall and a urinal, women's is just a toilet and sink. Both have changing tables.

name: Union trust building
directions: Second floor, visible across from elevators and also next to the giant glass doors
comment: You have to enter through the side entrance I think on fifth street

name: Petsmart
directions: Down a short hallway in the back left corner of the store

name: Weyenberg Public Library
directions: A family bathroom around the corner from the Reference desk down a hallway off the children's area.
comment: Closed Sundays.

name: Rhythm and Cues
directions: Back left corner of bar.

name: Judea Reform Congregation
directions: To the right of the front door, across from the Rabbi's study.
comment: The front door is often locked during business hours.

name: The Theatre School at DePaul University
directions: First floor theatre lobby

name: Ferndale Area District Library
directions: In the children's area there's a unisex restroom
comment: The library supports transgender people so you can use the gendered restrooms as well and staff will support you in the event that another patron may complain

name: Outpost Natural Foods
comment: One mens room and one womens room, both single-stall with lockable doors. Multiple trans, nonbinary, and L/G/B staff present and supportive, several willing to act as bouncers if needed.

name: Dress Barn
directions: Back of the store, first hallway on the right, first door you come to.
comment: Ask an employee before heading back. The same hallway leads to the office and back stock. You don't have to buy anything, but browsing a little wouldn't hurt.

name: Arcana
directions: Back of the room
comment: Has prince symbol on doors

name: 21C Museum Hotel
directions: Second floor of the galleries.

name: Costco
directions: One restroom in the tires department near the service desk. You don't need a membership card to come in this way
comment: One restroom in the tires department near the service desk. You don't need a membership card to come in this way

name: IGADI LTD
directions: On the left hand wall in the main lobby.
comment: No purchase or interaction required.

name: Mattie B's Public House
comment: Try the pizza while you're there!! It's great!

name: Starbucks
directions: It's right when you open the door.

name: Eastside Food Co-op
directions: Down the hall next to the coffee bar.
comment: EFC also has a Family restroom.

name: Richmond Ace Hardware
directions: At the very front of the store, immediately to the right after walking through the front doors
comment: Simply ask the cashier "do you have a bathroom?" and we'll point it out to you and that'll be it! Some may say "Have a good day!" afterwards just as a heads up to people who don't like/get anxious about unexpected social interaction!!

name: Baylor Family Medicine
directions: Inside VERY trans-friendly primary care clinic
comment: Meant for patients, but in an emergency, we'd love to help

name: Church of the Holy Trinity
directions: Gender neutral accessible washroom just inside south door.
comment: LGBT+ church outside Eaton centre sometimes open to drop in tourists as well as services and concerts.

name: Speedway
directions: Right in the back of store.
comment: Get the key from clerks.

name: CCRI Knight Campus
directions: 1st floor (above ground floor) in round building
comment: Super secluded space no worries about anything!!

name: Meijer
directions: In front of store by deli there is a single stall "family" restroom.

name: Seattle Healing Arts Building
directions: Third floor

name: Andrews Library
directions: Front door in Gualt
comment: Open to public but weird hours when school isn't in session

name: The Local Store
directions: Towards the back, to the right of the cash register, past the music area on the right

name: Aurora Regional Fire Museum
directions: 2nd floor restrooms are gendered single stall but not accessible. First floor bathrooms are gendered multi-stall but are accessible

name: Optimystical Studios
directions: Just ask staff to use restroom.
comment: Business door does not have automatic open, but knock if needed and staff can open for you. Store is a safe space.

name: Mt. Pleasant Animal Shelter
directions: On the right side of the lobby next to the dog kennel door
comment: Best if you don't just use the bathroom, so maybe donate a few dollars for the animals. Also a great LGBT place to volunteer

name: Jewel Supermarket
directions: In front of store by North side entrance

name: Kitsap Regional Library
directions: Towards the back of the library. Keys are located by the computers. Family/Unisex restrooms.
comment: The library is a safe/warm/dry place for everyone.

name: Naskart
directions: To the left of the entrance.

name: Mt. Pleasant Animal Shelter
directions: On the right side of the lobby next to the door to the dog kennel
comment: They probably won't like it if you just come to use the bathroom but you can always give a few dollars to the animals. LGBT friendly place to volunteer as well.

name: Mt. Pleasant Animal Shelter
directions: On the right side of the lobby next to the door to the dog kennel
comment: They probably won't like it if you just come to use the bathroom but you can always give a few dollars to the animals. LGBT friendly place to volunteer as well.

name: Kaliesia Tea Lounge
directions: 1st floor in the back past the cash register and down the hallway

name: Pizza Pretzel Creations
directions: To the right, before the counter to order food
comment: Two unisex restrooms with locking doors

name: Durham Technical Community College
directions: Three locations: Across from library in Building 5 (single stall), third floor of Building 10, and near front entrance of Building 4.

name: Kishwaukee Hospital
directions: Between the emergency room and lobby. Walk down past the gift shop.

name: Kishwaukee Hospital
directions: Hallway between emergency room and lobby past the giftshop

name: Incognito Tattoo
directions: Through the door to the left of the counter
comment: Single occupancy restroom with locking door for piercing and tattoo customers.

name: Colt's Timeless Tattoos
directions: Through the shop and into the hallway of the main house. You'll know the door because it will say "unisex bathroom" on it.
comment: The door requires a key, but usually whoever is working is happy to pass it on to you, regardless of whether you are getting work done. This may be less true if there is only one artist working, if they have to stop tattooing to direct you.

name: Walmart
directions: Family bathroom in back of store

name: Center for Performing Arts
directions: On the first floor near the box office
comment: Use anytime! Building closes around 11pm

name: Kaiser Permanente/East Bay Obstetrics and Gynecology
directions: First floor, directly by the entrance.
comment: Have yet to see anyone asked for Kaiser ID or anything.

name: Lee Harvey's
directions: One out in the patio area and one inside. Both are single stalls & unisex.
comment: Use the one outside; the one inside usually smells terrible.

name: Central Oregon Community College Bend Campus
comment: This is the community college campus.

name: Johnson Public House
directions: All the way to the back, past the fridge. You can also enter from the back door (accessible from a driveway off of Paterson).

name: Bloom bake shop
directions: Past the counter

name: Fenway Health
comment: LGBTQ health Center with a bathroom on every floor. Has elevators

name: COCC Redmond Campus
comment: This is the community college campus

name: First Church Boston
comment: Unitarian church

name: Jo-Ann Fabrics and Crafts
directions: In the far back, on the left wall
comment: Most likely do not need to be a paying customer. The sign says unisex, I believe it is a singles tall.

name: Sweet Home Bar and Grill
directions: In the back.
comment: Very trans friendly establishment. Ignore the gendered signs.

name: ECRI Institute
directions: first floor of "new" IT area has a single-person powder room (handicap accessible). Spacious and has a lock for privacy.
comment: Visitors will most likely be directed to gendered, multi-toilet stalls just off of reception area but if your business takes you near the HD labs or new IT area, employees won't even blink an eye if you need to duck into the single-person bathroom

name: Lasagna
directions: At the back of the restaurant, downstairs
comment: Need to be a customer at the restaurant. Sit down restaurant.

name: Das Lokal
directions: At the back of the restaurant by the bar.
comment: For paying customers. These restrooms are unisex. They are somewhat narrow so not really accessible.

name: Das Lokal
directions: At the back of the restaurant by the bar.
comment: For paying customers. These restrooms are unisex. They are somewhat narrow so not really accessible.
